+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DxPc6rP2Upy8AhwoGbaaLa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015rDVf6jgrpH9o1Vjca5nhU","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-08-fts-search.md","content":"# Full-Text Search Feature Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Add SQLite FTS5-based full-text search and autocomplete suggest endpoints to the existing note-taking API.\n\n**Architecture:** Create an FTS5 virtual table (`notes_fts`) as a content table linked to `notes`. Use SQLite triggers (INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE) to keep the FTS index in sync. Add two new route handlers for search and suggest that query the FTS table with BM25 ranking and snippet highlighting. Special characters in user queries are sanitized before being passed to FTS5 MATCH.\n\n**Tech Stack:** SQLite FTS5 (via better-sqlite3), Express routes, TypeScript\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Add FTS5 Virtual Table and Triggers to Database Setup\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/db.ts:10-19` (add FTS table creation and triggers after notes table creation)\n\n**Step 1: Add FTS5 table and triggers**\n\nIn `src/db.ts`, after the `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes` block, add:\n\n```typescript\n// Create FTS5 virtual table for full-text search\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes_fts USING fts5(\n    title,\n    body,\n    content='notes',\n    content_rowid='id'\n  )\n`);\n\n// Triggers to keep FTS index in sync\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE TRIGGER IF NOT EXISTS notes_ai AFTER INSERT ON notes BEGIN\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(rowid, title, body) VALUES (new.id, new.title, new.body);\n  END\n`);\n\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE TRIGGER IF NOT EXISTS notes_ad AFTER DELETE ON notes BEGIN\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(notes_fts, rowid, title, body) VALUES('delete', old.id, old.title, old.body);\n  END\n`);\n\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE TRIGGER IF NOT EXISTS notes_au AFTER UPDATE ON notes BEGIN\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(notes_fts, rowid, title, body) VALUES('delete', old.id, old.title, old.body);\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(rowid, title, body) VALUES (new.id, new.title, new.body);\n  END\n`);\n```\n\n**Step 2: Populate FTS index from existing data in seedDatabase**\n\nIn `src/db.ts`, at the end of the `seedDatabase` function (after `insertMany(notes)`), add:\n\n```typescript\n// Rebuild FTS index from existing data\ndb.exec(`INSERT INTO notes_fts(notes_fts) VALUES('rebuild')`);\n```\n\n**Step 3: Run existing tests to verify nothing breaks**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run tests/notes.test.ts`\nExpected: All 15 tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Add Search Endpoint `GET /notes/search?q=<query>`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/routes.ts` (add search route BEFORE the `/:id` route to avoid route conflicts)\n\n**Step 1: Add search route**\n\nAdd these routes BEFORE the `router.get('/notes/:id', ...)` handler. Import `SearchResult` and `SuggestResult` from models. Add a helper to sanitize FTS5 queries.\n\nAt the top of `createRoutes`, add a sanitize helper:\n\n```typescript\nfunction sanitizeFtsQuery(query: string): string {\n  // Remove FTS5 special characters that could cause syntax errors\n  // Keep quoted phrases intact for phrase matching\n  if (query.startsWith('\"') && query.endsWith('\"')) {\n    return query; // Pass through quoted phrases\n  }\n  // Remove special FTS5 operators/characters\n  return query.replace(/[*^(){}[\\]:!&|+\\-<>~@#$/\\\\]/g, ' ').replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim();\n}\n```\n\nAdd the search route:\n\n```typescript\n// GET /notes/search - Full-text search\nrouter.get('/notes/search', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n  try {\n    const q = req.query.q as string | undefined;\n    if (!q || q.trim() === '') {\n      throw new ValidationError('Search query is required');\n    }\n\n    const page = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.page as string) || 1);\n    const perPage = 20;\n    const offset = (page - 1) * perPage;\n\n    const sanitized = sanitizeFtsQuery(q.trim());\n    if (!sanitized) {\n      res.json({ results: [], total: 0, page, perPage });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Count total matches\n    const countStmt = db.prepare(`\n      SELECT COUNT(*) as total FROM notes_fts WHERE notes_fts MATCH ?\n    `);\n\n    let total: number;\n    try {\n      total = (countStmt.get(sanitized) as { total: number }).total;\n    } catch {\n      // If FTS query syntax is invalid, return empty results\n      res.json({ results: [], total: 0, page, perPage });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Search with ranking and snippets\n    const searchStmt = db.prepare(`\n      SELECT\n        notes_fts.rowid as id,\n        notes.title,\n        snippet(notes_fts, 1, '<mark>', '</mark>', '...', 32) as snippet,\n        rank\n      FROM notes_fts\n      JOIN notes ON notes.id = notes_fts.rowid\n      WHERE notes_fts MATCH ?\n      ORDER BY rank\n      LIMIT ? OFFSET ?\n    `);\n\n    let results: SearchResult[];\n    try {\n      results = searchStmt.all(sanitized, perPage, offset) as SearchResult[];\n    } catch {\n      results = [];\n    }\n\n    res.json({ results, total, page, perPage });\n  } catch (err) {\n    next(err);\n  }\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add suggest route**\n\n```typescript\n// GET /notes/search/suggest - Autocomplete suggestions\nrouter.get('/notes/search/suggest', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n  try {\n    const q = req.query.q as string | undefined;\n    if (!q || q.trim() === '') {\n      throw new ValidationError('Search query is required');\n    }\n\n    const sanitized = sanitizeFtsQuery(q.trim());\n    if (!sanitized) {\n      res.json({ results: [] });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Use prefix matching with *\n    const prefixQuery = sanitized.split(/\\s+/).map(term => `${term}*`).join(' ');\n\n    const suggestStmt = db.prepare(`\n      SELECT\n        notes_fts.rowid as id,\n        notes.title\n      FROM notes_fts\n      JOIN notes ON notes.id = notes_fts.rowid\n      WHERE notes_fts MATCH ?\n      ORDER BY rank\n      LIMIT 5\n    `);\n\n    let results: SuggestResult[];\n    try {\n      results = suggestStmt.all(prefixQuery) as SuggestResult[];\n    } catch {\n      results = [];\n    }\n\n    res.json({ results });\n  } catch (err) {\n    next(err);\n  }\n});\n```\n\n**Step 3: Update imports in routes.ts**\n\nAdd `SearchResult` and `SuggestResult` to the imports from models:\n\n```typescript\nimport { Note, NoteInput, SearchResult, SuggestResult } from './models.js';\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Run All Tests\n\n**Step 1: Run the full test suite**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run`\nExpected: All 35 tests pass (15 CRUD + 20 search)\n\n**Step 2: Fix any failures**\n\nIf any tests fail, analyze the error messages and fix accordingly.\n\n---\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":212,"cache_read_input_tokens":44634,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":212},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1e75533-e599-467a-8048-7275d8a4805b","uuid":"2a62b994-8693-4fe7-9825-104da083aa27"}
+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015rDVf6jgrpH9o1Vjca5nhU","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-08-fts-search.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1e75533-e599-467a-8048-7275d8a4805b","uuid":"924b6c4f-11b4-4fb2-bf71-c43c2ee78a0c","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-08-fts-search.md","content":"# Full-Text Search Feature Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Add SQLite FTS5-based full-text search and autocomplete suggest endpoints to the existing note-taking API.\n\n**Architecture:** Create an FTS5 virtual table (`notes_fts`) as a content table linked to `notes`. Use SQLite triggers (INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE) to keep the FTS index in sync. Add two new route handlers for search and suggest that query the FTS table with BM25 ranking and snippet highlighting. Special characters in user queries are sanitized before being passed to FTS5 MATCH.\n\n**Tech Stack:** SQLite FTS5 (via better-sqlite3), Express routes, TypeScript\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Add FTS5 Virtual Table and Triggers to Database Setup\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/db.ts:10-19` (add FTS table creation and triggers after notes table creation)\n\n**Step 1: Add FTS5 table and triggers**\n\nIn `src/db.ts`, after the `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes` block, add:\n\n```typescript\n// Create FTS5 virtual table for full-text search\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes_fts USING fts5(\n    title,\n    body,\n    content='notes',\n    content_rowid='id'\n  )\n`);\n\n// Triggers to keep FTS index in sync\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE TRIGGER IF NOT EXISTS notes_ai AFTER INSERT ON notes BEGIN\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(rowid, title, body) VALUES (new.id, new.title, new.body);\n  END\n`);\n\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE TRIGGER IF NOT EXISTS notes_ad AFTER DELETE ON notes BEGIN\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(notes_fts, rowid, title, body) VALUES('delete', old.id, old.title, old.body);\n  END\n`);\n\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE TRIGGER IF NOT EXISTS notes_au AFTER UPDATE ON notes BEGIN\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(notes_fts, rowid, title, body) VALUES('delete', old.id, old.title, old.body);\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(rowid, title, body) VALUES (new.id, new.title, new.body);\n  END\n`);\n```\n\n**Step 2: Populate FTS index from existing data in seedDatabase**\n\nIn `src/db.ts`, at the end of the `seedDatabase` function (after `insertMany(notes)`), add:\n\n```typescript\n// Rebuild FTS index from existing data\ndb.exec(`INSERT INTO notes_fts(notes_fts) VALUES('rebuild')`);\n```\n\n**Step 3: Run existing tests to verify nothing breaks**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run tests/notes.test.ts`\nExpected: All 15 tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Add Search Endpoint `GET /notes/search?q=<query>`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/routes.ts` (add search route BEFORE the `/:id` route to avoid route conflicts)\n\n**Step 1: Add search route**\n\nAdd these routes BEFORE the `router.get('/notes/:id', ...)` handler. Import `SearchResult` and `SuggestResult` from models. Add a helper to sanitize FTS5 queries.\n\nAt the top of `createRoutes`, add a sanitize helper:\n\n```typescript\nfunction sanitizeFtsQuery(query: string): string {\n  // Remove FTS5 special characters that could cause syntax errors\n  // Keep quoted phrases intact for phrase matching\n  if (query.startsWith('\"') && query.endsWith('\"')) {\n    return query; // Pass through quoted phrases\n  }\n  // Remove special FTS5 operators/characters\n  return query.replace(/[*^(){}[\\]:!&|+\\-<>~@#$/\\\\]/g, ' ').replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim();\n}\n```\n\nAdd the search route:\n\n```typescript\n// GET /notes/search - Full-text search\nrouter.get('/notes/search', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n  try {\n    const q = req.query.q as string | undefined;\n    if (!q || q.trim() === '') {\n      throw new ValidationError('Search query is required');\n    }\n\n    const page = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.page as string) || 1);\n    const perPage = 20;\n    const offset = (page - 1) * perPage;\n\n    const sanitized = sanitizeFtsQuery(q.trim());\n    if (!sanitized) {\n      res.json({ results: [], total: 0, page, perPage });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Count total matches\n    const countStmt = db.prepare(`\n      SELECT COUNT(*) as total FROM notes_fts WHERE notes_fts MATCH ?\n    `);\n\n    let total: number;\n    try {\n      total = (countStmt.get(sanitized) as { total: number }).total;\n    } catch {\n      // If FTS query syntax is invalid, return empty results\n      res.json({ results: [], total: 0, page, perPage });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Search with ranking and snippets\n    const searchStmt = db.prepare(`\n      SELECT\n        notes_fts.rowid as id,\n        notes.title,\n        snippet(notes_fts, 1, '<mark>', '</mark>', '...', 32) as snippet,\n        rank\n      FROM notes_fts\n      JOIN notes ON notes.id = notes_fts.rowid\n      WHERE notes_fts MATCH ?\n      ORDER BY rank\n      LIMIT ? OFFSET ?\n    `);\n\n    let results: SearchResult[];\n    try {\n      results = searchStmt.all(sanitized, perPage, offset) as SearchResult[];\n    } catch {\n      results = [];\n    }\n\n    res.json({ results, total, page, perPage });\n  } catch (err) {\n    next(err);\n  }\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add suggest route**\n\n```typescript\n// GET /notes/search/suggest - Autocomplete suggestions\nrouter.get('/notes/search/suggest', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n  try {\n    const q = req.query.q as string | undefined;\n    if (!q || q.trim() === '') {\n      throw new ValidationError('Search query is required');\n    }\n\n    const sanitized = sanitizeFtsQuery(q.trim());\n    if (!sanitized) {\n      res.json({ results: [] });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Use prefix matching with *\n    const prefixQuery = sanitized.split(/\\s+/).map(term => `${term}*`).join(' ');\n\n    const suggestStmt = db.prepare(`\n      SELECT\n        notes_fts.rowid as id,\n        notes.title\n      FROM notes_fts\n      JOIN notes ON notes.id = notes_fts.rowid\n      WHERE notes_fts MATCH ?\n      ORDER BY rank\n      LIMIT 5\n    `);\n\n    let results: SuggestResult[];\n    try {\n      results = suggestStmt.all(prefixQuery) as SuggestResult[];\n    } catch {\n      results = [];\n    }\n\n    res.json({ results });\n  } catch (err) {\n    next(err);\n  }\n});\n```\n\n**Step 3: Update imports in routes.ts**\n\nAdd `SearchResult` and `SuggestResult` to the imports from models:\n\n```typescript\nimport { Note, NoteInput, SearchResult, SuggestResult } from './models.js';\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Run All Tests\n\n**Step 1: Run the full test suite**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run`\nExpected: All 35 tests pass (15 CRUD + 20 search)\n\n**Step 2: Fix any failures**\n\nIf any tests fail, analyze the error messages and fix accordingly.\n\n---\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
